segments.title: Density Basic Explanation
segments.summary: Explains density as a ratio of mass to volume, measured in kg/m³ or g/cm³. Describes density as a measure of how packed or crowded something is.

segments.title: Density Effects on Floating
segments.summary: Explains how objects with lower density float while those with higher density sink. Uses examples of oil floating on water and iron bolt sinking.

segments.title: Air Density Changes
segments.summary: Describes how air density varies with altitude, with lower density at higher altitudes. Explains density differences from sea level to airplane cruising altitude.

segments.title: Water Density Properties
segments.summary: Explains water's unique density properties, with maximum density at 4°C. Describes how ice forms with lower density than liquid water, causing it to float.

segments.title: Earth's Density Layers
segments.summary: Describes how Earth's layers formed based on density differences, with denser materials like iron sinking to form the core while lighter silicates floated to form the crust.
